response: Adoption agencies do not expect the entire cost of an adoption to be paid "up front." For example, an agency might divide payment into three portions, with one-third of the total amount to be paid when filing the initial application, one- third at completion of the home study process, and one- third when the child is placed and the post placement supervision period begins. Want to hear more?
